    "Unknown": "II. Here is the proffer which he made to the chief priests; he went to them, and said, What will ye give me?\nv.\nv. 4,\n4. They would not pitch upon a place without direction from him, and from him they had direction; he sent them to such a man (",
    "Benjamin Keach": "Because the same laws bind all sorts of persons, within the compass of that kingdom or its jurisdiction, there is not one law for the great ones, (or for the rich) and another for the meaner sort; and as it is thus in an earthly kingdom, it is in Christ\u2019s visible church, all are under the same laws, precepts and ordinances.\n4. Because the doctrine, faith, order, rule, and government lead to heaven, promoting an holy and heavenly life, and to prepare us for heaven."
